body:
If I'm not mistaken, older versions of VSCode displayed configuration settings in the order they were specified in `package.json`. This is no longer the case and probably related to the switch to a visual config editor.

However, ordering configuration settings alphabetically does not always make sense. I prefer grouping related properties and to logically guide a user through them.

**Example:**

```json
"configuration": {
  ...
  "properties": {
    "nsis.pathToMakensis": {
      "type": "string",
      "default": null,
      "description": "Specify the path to makensis"
    },
    "nsis.compilerArguments": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "default": [],
      "description": "Specify custom compiler arguments"
    },
    "nsis.alwaysOpenBuildTask": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "default": true,
      "description": "Specify whether to open the newly created build task"
    }
  }
}
```

These options are now displayed in the following order:

1. Always Open Build Task
2. Compiler Arguments
3. Path To Makensis

Specifying `pathToMakensis` is the most important setting in this example. Since the `compilerArguments` setting depends on a path to be specified, it would make more sense to have it after the `pathToMakensis` setting. Also in this example, there is the `alwaysOpenBuildTask` setting, which is a setting most people won't care about. Being less important, it makes no sense to have it displayed first.

Configuration settings for the Atom editor have a very similar format to that of VSCode. They allow specifying the `order` in which the settings appear.

**Example:**

```json
"configuration": {
  ...
  "properties": {
    "nsis.pathToMakensis": {
      "type": "string",
      "default": null,
      "description": "Specify the path to makensis",
      "order": 1
    },
    "nsis.compilerArguments": {
      "type": "array",
      "items": {
        "type": "string"
      },
      "default": [],
      "description": "Specify custom compiler arguments",
      "order": 2
    },
    "nsis.alwaysOpenBuildTask": {
      "type": "boolean",
      "default": true,
      "description": "Specify whether to open the newly created build task",
      "order": 3
    }
  }
}
```

It would be useful, if VSCode had the same to specify the order!

Now that we have support for [`IURLService#create()`](https://github.com/Microsoft/vscode/blob/a06015b53693d2f8a5a83cacff0da25b025f9e6f/src/vs/platform/url/common/urlService.ts#L19) we should try to get the window ID into the URI so that we can prefer to open the link in that window.

Today it seems we simply open in the last active window, which might not be right.

